name: NSCountedSet
desc: A mutable, unordered collection of distinct objects that may appear more than once in the collection.

items.name: init(array: [Any])
items.desc: Returns a counted set object initialized with the contents of a given array.

items.name: init(set: Set<AnyHashable>)
items.desc: Returns a counted set object initialized with the contents of a given set.

items.name: init(capacity: Int)
items.desc: Returns a counted set object initialized with enough memory to hold a given number of objects.

items.name: func add(Any)
items.desc: Adds a given object to the set.

items.name: func remove(Any)
items.desc: Removes a given object from the set.

items.name: func count(for: Any) -> Int
items.desc: Returns the count associated with a given object in the set.

items.name: func objectEnumerator() -> NSEnumerator
items.desc: Returns an enumerator object that lets you access each object in the set once, independent of its count.
